cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CR, cs.DB 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with Statistical Relational Learning, which is an emerging area in AI. It also involves combining logical and statistical AI, which is a common theme in AI research. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as both MLN and PSL are probabilistic graphical models used in machine learning. 

cs.CL (Computation and Language) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with natural language processing and the use of logic in language understanding. 

cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the use of weights in logic, which is relevant to cryptographic protocols. 

Finally, cs.DB (Databases) is also a possible sub-category as both MLN and PSL are used in probabilistic databases.
